#compdef redis-viewer
# ============================================================================
# _redis-viewer — zsh completion for saltfishpr's redis-viewer, a Go
#                  Bubble Tea TUI for browsing Redis keys / values
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/saltfishpr/redis-viewer
#   Author     : saltfishpr  <saltfishpr@gmail.com>
#   License    : MIT
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/saltfishpr/redis-viewer
#   Binary     : redis-viewer  (rootCmd.Use = "redis-viewer" in
#                                cmd/root.go;  built from root
#                                main.go calling cmd.Execute)
#   Last push  : 2026-04-21
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   redis-viewer is "a tool to view Redis data in terminal" —
#   saltfishpr's Bubble Tea (charmbracelet/bubbletea) full-screen
#   TUI that connects to a Redis instance and lets the operator
#   browse keys, inspect values of every Redis type (string, list,
#   hash, set, zset, stream, JSON), filter by pattern, and switch
#   databases without leaving the terminal.  Connection details
#   (host, port, password, DB index, page_size, etc.) live in a
#   YAML config file (default `$HOME/.redis-viewer.yaml`) loaded
#   through viper, with env-var overrides via `viper.AutomaticEnv`.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/root.go spf13/cobra
#                       rootCmd + viper bind)
#   redis-viewer [OPTIONS]
#
#   redis-viewer has no subcommands;  the bare invocation opens
#   the TUI directly.
#
#   Options:
#     -c, --config <FILE>      Config file
#                                [default: $HOME/.redis-viewer.yaml]
#
#   Standard cobra auto-flags:
#     -h, --help               Show help
#
#   Environment variables:  viper `AutomaticEnv` reads any
#   environment variable matching a config key (uppercase).
#   The defaults seeded by `initConfig` are:
#     mode                     "client"  (override via `MODE` env
#                              or the `mode:` YAML key)
#     page_size                20        (override via `PAGE_SIZE`
#                              or `page_size:` YAML key)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/go-redis/redis/v8 v8.11.5`
#   declared in go.mod — the canonical Go Redis client maintained
#   by the go-redis organization (redis/go-redis;  v8 is the
#   long-term-supported pre-context API, v9 is the current line).
#   go-redis provides typed `Client` / `ClusterClient` / `Ring` /
#   `Sentinel` / `UniversalClient` constructors, full RESP2 + RESP3
#   protocol coverage, idiomatic Go context.Context integration,
#   pipelining, transactions (MULTI/EXEC), pub/sub, Streams,
#   Cluster + Sentinel topology, and OpenTelemetry hooks.
#   redis-viewer's `internal/conf/` constructs a `redis.NewClient
#   (&redis.Options{Addr, Password, DB, ...})` per browse session
#   and uses `client.Scan`, `client.Type`, and per-type readers
#   (LRange / HGetAll / SMembers / ZRange / XRange) to populate
#   the Bubble Tea model.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/saltfishpr/redis-viewer/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/go-redis/redis/v8 v8.11.5
#       → github.com/spf13/cobra v1.10.2
#     gh api repos/saltfishpr/redis-viewer/contents/cmd/root.go
#       → rootCmd.Use = "redis-viewer"
#       → -c/--config flag bound to viper
#   This entry is the Go=134 leader bump that continues Axis 79
#   (Redis Client Library) opened at R905 with Rust=redis 0.27
#   (jiawesoft/jiascheduler).
#
#   No completion for `redis-viewer` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_redis-viewer() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(-c --config)'{-c+,--config=}'[config file (default $HOME/.redis-viewer.yaml)]:config file:_files -g "*.{yaml,yml}"' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]'
}

_redis-viewer "$@"
